    "narrative": "The Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is anchored by **Corbin Carroll**, who commands the highest score of the day (81.24). Despite a challenging matchup against Max Scherzer, **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a strong lineup position (#2) and positive platoon metrics, making him a must-start as we hunt for stolen base efficiency. **Tyler Soderstrom** (76.91) represents our most favorable matchup against a struggling pitcher in Erick Fedde; his score is significantly elevated by a 19% boost from Fedde\u2019s projected xERA and a generous park environment. **James Wood** (73.32) also provides elite value out of the leadoff spot, capitalizing on a favorable matchup against Adrian Houser to balance our offensive floor.\n\nThe most difficult decision today was excluding **Seiya Suzuki** (51.44), who fell just outside the optimal starting rotation. While **Seiya Suzuki** offers reliable daily output, his matchup against Freddy Peralta is dampened by a weak BvP history and a negative park adjustment, ultimately losing his spot to the higher upside of **Jose Caballero** and **Mickey Moniak**, the latter of whom earns a significant boost from park factors and platoon advantages. We are also keeping a close eye on the wind conditions impacting **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino**; the current \"Wind In\" advisory is suppressing their ceilings, making them riskier plays than their base projections suggest.\n\nRisk remains elevated across the board due to the \"Lineup Pending\" status for many of our assets, including **Dalton Rushing**, **Luis Campusano**, **Alex Freeland**, **Max Muncy**, **Brice Turang**, **James Wood**, and **Mickey Moniak**. While we have assigned assumed batting orders, any late changes\u2014particularly for **Brice Turang** and **James Wood**\u2014will shift our daily efficiency. We are also proceeding with caution regarding **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Vinnie Pasquantino**, as the unfavorable wind at their venue could turn potential homers into long outs, forcing us to lean heavily on the speed of **Corbin Carroll** and **Jose Caballero** to carry the category scoring today.",
